                     <interp inst="t18311201-196-person1568" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I saw the prisoner in Bunhill-row; he turned up Banner-street, and I took him - he had these trousers, waistcoat, and braces on.</p>
               <p>SAMUEL RADDLE. I lodged in the room; part of these are mine.</p>
               <p>A. S. WILSON. These articles are mine.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I was out of work; it is my first offence.</p>
